  "prompt": "What are some songs which include underwater sounds?",
  "response": "Here are some songs that incorporate underwater sounds or themes related to water:\n\n1. **\"Under the Sea\" by Samuel E. Wright (from The Little Mermaid)** - This classic Disney song features playful underwater sounds fitting its aquatic theme.\n\n2. **\"Octopus's Garden\" by The Beatles** - The track has a whimsical feel and includes sounds that evoke an underwater atmosphere.\n\n3. **\"Beyond the Sea\" by Bobby Darin** - While not strictly featuring underwater sounds, the song's theme is heavily connected to the ocean.\n\n4. **\"Aqua Boogie\" by Parliament** - This funk song explicitly references underwater themes and includes various aquatic sound effects.\n\n5. **\"Underwater\" by Mika** - This song includes soundscapes that resemble underwater acoustics and is rich in metaphorical references to the ocean.\n\n6. **\"Breathe\" by Pink Floyd** - Though more atmospheric, the song features sounds that might remind listeners of depths and echoes, reminiscent of underwater environments.\n\n7. **\"Song of the Sea\" by Lisa Hannigan (from the movie Song of the Sea)** - This emotive track features a dreamy feel that evokes a sense of being underwater.\n\n8. **\"Submerged\" by Angela McCluskey** - The song\u2019s ethereal quality and instrumentation can create an underwater vibe.\n\n9. **\"Underwater\" by R\u00dcF\u00dcS DU SOL** - This electronic track features synths that can create a feeling of being submerged.\n\n10. **\"The Ocean\" by Mike Perry feat. Shy Martin** - While this song focuses on the beach and ocean themes, the sounds and vibes resonate with underwater imagery.\n\nThese songs utilize sounds and themes that conjure an underwater atmosphere in various ways, from literal sound effects to metaphorical references.",
